rman-of-tata-trusts-after-ratan-tata-s-passing-124101100444_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fpeople%2Fnoel-tata-elected-chairman-of-tata-trusts-after-ratan-tata-s-passing-124101100444_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ratan%20Tata%E2%80%99s%20successor%3A%20Noel%20Tata%20appointed%20chairman%20of%20Tata%20Trusts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728634800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114143677%2Cimgsize-25342.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fratan-tatas-successor-noel-tata-appointed-chairman-of-tata-trusts%2Farticleshow%2F114143698.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Noel%20Tata%2C%20aged%2067%2C%20has%20been%20appointed%20chairman%20of%20Tata%20Trusts%20after%20the%20passing%20of%20Ratan%20Tata.%20Noel%20holds%20several%20significant%20positions%20within%20the%20Tata%20Group%2C%20including%20Chairman%20of%20Trent%20and%20Voltas.%20His%20extensive%20leadership%20background%20spans%20four%20decades%2C%20and%20his%20tenure%20has%20seen%20notable%20successes%20for%20various%20Tata%20companies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20from%20Sweden%20to%20the%20US.%20I've%20found%20Americans%20to%20be%20friendlier%20and%20I%20enjoy%20the%20work%20hustle.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223022%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20wearing%20a%20blue%20baseball%20cap%20crouching%20down%20in%20a%20wood.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67042df2a7031864927ff5fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222267%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOlivia%20Tapper%20generally%20prefers%20her%20life%20in%20the%20US%20to%20Sweden.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Olivia%20Tapper%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOlivia%20Tapper%20settled%20in%20the%20US%20in%202004%20after%20intermittently%20studying%20and%20working%20there%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%2029-year-old%20said%20she%20sought%20a%20%26quot%3Bdifferent%2C%20more%20dedicated%26quot%3B%20work%20culture%20and%20found%20it%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20misses%20parts%20of%20her%20life%20in%20Scandinavia%20but%20enjoys%20being%20more%20openly%20ambitious%20about%20her%20future.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Olivia%20Tapper%2C%2029%2C%20who%20currently%20lives%20in%20Austin%2C%20Texas.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20vacations%2C%20I%20first%20stayed%20in%20the%20US%20in%202019.%20I%20was%20researching%20a%20master's%20thesis%20as%20part%20of%20my%20degree%20in%20my%20native%20Sweden%20and%20lived%20in%20New%20York%20for%20a%20year.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20venture%20out%20into%20the%20world%20and%20experience%20somewhere%20else.%20Everything%20about%20the%20US%20compelled%20me%20to%20live%20there%20permanently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%20%E2%80%94%20after%20splitting%20our%20time%20working%20between%20Europe%20and%20America%20%E2%80%94%20my%20husband%2C%20Thomas%2C%2033%2C%20made%20the%20big%20step%20of%20immigrating%20permanently%20after%20finding%20a%20house%20in%20Austin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20run%20two%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dtcseoagency.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20online%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20interact%20with%20many%20clients%20stateside%2C%20mostly%20business%20owners%20who%20market%20goods%20as%20diverse%20as%20candy%20and%20activewear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20dedicated%20to%20building%20their%20personal%20brands.%20They%20hustle.%20They'll%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-happens-when-you-block-someone-on-whatsapp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eping%20me%20on%20WhatsApp%20%3C%2Fa%3Eover%20the%20weekend%20if%20they%20need%20something%20done.%20It's%20a%20different%20career%20mindset.%20Like%20them%2C%20I%20enjoy%20working%20at%20that%20tempo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20great%20job%20in%20Sweden%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20a%20strategic%20business%20developer%20in%20the%20IT%20department%20of%20a%20global%20company%20%E2%80%94%20and%20loved%20my%20boss.%20I%20didn't%20really%20%3Cem%3Eneed%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20move%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20quite%20happy%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20as%20if%20things%20moved%20slowly.%20Sweden%20has%20a%20big%20consensus%20culture.%20It%20takes%20a%20long%20time%20for%20decisions%20and%20projects%20to%20be%20made%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20a%20little%20bit%20stuck%20in%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228955e8b6-7dc2-45fe-8168-0b5eb5434ff6%5C%22%3EMy%20job%20is%20my%20passion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20experience%2C%20Swedish%20society%20is%20not%20as%20individualistic%20as%20in%20the%20US.%20It's%20less%20focused%20on%20the%20person%20and%20their%20achievements.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20I%20graduated%20from%20college%2C%20there%20was%20no%20valedictorian%20at%20my%20school.%20There%20was%20no%20top%20of%20the%20class.%20You%20either%20passed%20or%20you%20didn't%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20there's%20a%20different%20cultural%20mindset%20in%20Sweden.%20Standing%20out%20or%20talking%20about%20achievement%20is%20often%20frowned%20upon.%20Tall-poppy%20syndrome%20%E2%80%94%20where%20pride%20is%20thought%20to%20come%20before%20a%20fall%20%E2%80%94%20is%20common.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.medicalnewstoday.com%2Farticles%2Ftall-poppy-syndrome%23origins%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETall-poppy%20syndrome%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20term%20that%20originated%20in%20ancient%20Rome%20and%20refers%20to%20wanting%20to%20cut%20down%20someone%20who%20stands%20out%20from%20a%20crowd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20go%20into%20things%20quite%20intensely.%20My%20job%20is%20my%20passion.%20I%20feel%20as%20if%20I'd%20be%20hindered%20if%20it%20wasn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20employed%20in%20Sweden%2C%20one%20of%20my%20former%20companies%20would%20practically%20shut%20down%20for%20four%20to%20six%20weeks%20over%20the%20summer.%20Everybody%20would%20be%20off%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20It's%20the%20traditional%20way%20that%20things%20have%20always%20been%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'd%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20out-of-office%20messages%2C%20which%20I%20found%20frustrating.%20My%20ex-boss%20said%20he%20thought%20it%20was%20odd%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20over%20the%20summer%20and%20take%20my%20vacation%20time%20when%20it%20suited%20me%20and%20was%20less%20crowded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20my%20experience%2C%20Swedish%20people%20are%20more%20guarded%20and%20reserved.%20Social%20interactions%20between%20strangers%20are%20rare%2C%20especially%20in%20public%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2260dd247a-8380-428a-9090-1ea95ccbd5b8%5C%22%3EI%20feel%20like%20I've%20outgrown%20my%20home%20country%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-sweden-from-the-us-culture-shock-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESweden%20is%20quiet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Thomas%20once%20said%20that%20if%20you%20were%20at%20the%20airport%20and%20dropped%20a%20penny%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20everyone%20would%20hear%20it.%20In%20Austin%2C%20public%20places%20are%20usually%20full%20of%20chatter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20friendly%20here.%20When%20we%20moved%20into%20our%20new%20house%2C%20the%20neighbors%20came%20around%20and%20introduced%20themselves.%20They%20brought%20goodies%20such%20as%20cupcakes.%20I%20never%20got%20to%20know%20my%20neighbors%20back%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20knock%20Sweden.%20I%20come%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstockholm-sweden-wood-city-sustai