to%20defend%20Israel%20from%20massive%20Iranian%20ballistic%20missile%20attacks%20and%20have%20used%20SM-3%20interceptors%20to%20defeat%20the%20incoming%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Standard%20Missile-3%20(SM-3)%2C%20a%20key%20air-defense%20interceptor%20made%20by%20RTX%20and%2C%20for%20some%20variants%2C%20Mitsubishi%20Heavy%20Industries%2C%20was%20first%20used%20in%20combat%20in%20April%20to%20shield%20Israel%20from%20an%20unprecedented%20attack%2C%20and%20then%20it%20saw%20combat%20again%20in%20October%20when%20Iran%20attacked%20a%20second%20time.%20The%20weapons%2C%20which%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissiledefenseadvocacy.org%2Fmissile-defense-systems-2%2Fmissile-defense-systems%2Fmissile-interceptors-by-cost%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20%2410%20million%20and%20almost%20%2430%20million%20depending%20on%20the%20variant%2C%20were%20fired%20by%20American%20destroyers%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavy%20leadership%20has%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-more-missiles-recently-got-first-kill-pacific-threats-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20needs%20many%20more%20SM-3s%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20counter%20threats%20in%20the%20Pacific%2C%20like%20China%2C%20but%20it's%20burning%20through%20these%20weapons%20in%20conflicts%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20without%20sufficient%20plans%20to%20replace%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArcher%20Macy%2C%20a%20retired%20Navy%20admiral%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20SM-3%20is%20particularly%20important%20in%20a%20fight%20with%20China%20because%20the%20interceptor%20is%20designed%20to%20counter%20China's%20%26quot%3Bapparent%20preference%20for%20long-range%20theater%20weapons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224c9357c3-a884-4847-9cdb-d806f5b64d97%5C%22%3EA%20key%20missile%20interceptor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SM-3%20is%20an%20element%20of%20the%20Navy's%20highly%20advanced%20Aegis%20Combat%20System.%20It%20uses%20a%20kinetic%20kill%20vehicle%20to%20hit%20and%20destroy%20short-%20to%20intermediate-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20during%20their%20mid-course%20phase%20of%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224752%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20guided%20missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Fitzgerald%20launches%20a%20Standard%20Missile-3%20during%20a%20joint%20ballistic%20missile%20defense%20exercise%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20Oct.%2025%2C%202012.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661ea5e049058e66935684ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223168%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUSS%20Fitzgerald%20launches%20an%20SM-3%20during%20an%20exercise%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20other%20air%20defenses%20on%20American%20warships%2C%20the%20SM-3%20can%20make%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-israel-exoatmospheric-missile-kill-capability-iran-attack-challenging-intercept-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexo-atmospheric%20intercepts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20it%20can%20eliminate%20targets%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SM-3%20has%20been%20tested%20dozens%20of%20times%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20but%20it%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-warships-used-weapon-combat-first-destroy-iranian-missiles-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaw%20combat%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20April%2013%2C%20when%20Navy%20warships%20used%20the%20interceptor%20to%20defend%20Israel%20from%20an%20Iranian%20attack%20involving%20a%20mix%20of%20over%20300%20missiles%20and%20drones.%20Then%2C%20less%20than%20six%20months%20later%2C%20on%20October%201%2C%20the%20SM-3%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-missile-new-combat-got-another-workout-against-iran-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eits%20second%20known%20appearance%20in%20combat%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Navy%20warships%20again%20defended%20Israel%2C%20this%20time%20from%20more%20than%20180%20Iranian%20ballistic%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20valuable%20SM-3s%20against%20Iranian%20missile%20attacks%2C%20which%20experts%20say%20are%20but%20a%20fraction%20of%20what%20the%20US%20might%20face%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firans-missile-strike-israel-just-fraction-what-china-could-do-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20war%20with%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20raised%20concerns%20among%20analysts%20that%20the%20US%20is%20not%20producing%20sufficient%20numbers%20of%20the%20weapons%20to%20ensure%20readiness%20for%20a%20potential%20great-power%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20far%20below%20rates%20of%20production%20to%20support%20a%20high-end%20conflict%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20McGrath%2C%20a%20retired%20naval%20officer%20and%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20The%20FerryBridge%20Group%20LLC%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20explaining%20that%20interceptor%20missiles%2C%20like%20the%20SM-3%2C%20%26quot%3Bplay%20a%20key%20role%26quot%3B%20in%20protecting%20and%20sustaining%20US%20seapower%20in%20a%20war%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20just%20the%20SM-3%20that%20the%20Navy%20is%20using%20up%20battling%20foes%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22USS%20Lake%20Erie%20launches%20an%20SM-3.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6707d3ba3f2165d716dfc964%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222143%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUSS%20Lake%20Erie%20launches%20an%20SM-3.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20US%20Navy%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20American%20warships%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-battles-best-iranian-tech-red-sea-admiral-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshooting%20down%20missiles%20and%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20by%20the%20Houthis%2C%20an%20Iranian%20proxy%20group%20in%20Yemen%20that's%20been%20attacking%20merchant%20shipping%20lanes%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20and%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Navy's%20counter-Houthi%20campaign%2C%20American%20warships%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-aircraft-spotted-sm6-missile-newly-tested-in-combat-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpended%20other%20interceptors%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Standard%20Missile%20family%2C%20like%20the%20SM-2%20and%20SM-6%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0both%20of%20which%20would%20still%20be%20needed%20in%20great%20quantities%20for%20a%20major%20war%20in%20the%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20closer%20you%20get%20to%20China%2C%20or%20to%20any%20threat%20country%2C%20your%20ranges%20become%20shorter%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Macy%2C%20a%20non-resident%20senior%20associate%20with%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies'%20Missile%20Defense%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20short-range%20engagement%2C%20China's%20missiles%20wouldn't%20need%20to%20travel%20as%20high%2C%20and%20they%20would%20likely%20have%20shorter%20flight%20times%20and%20travel%20at%20slower%20speeds.%20In%20that%20situation%2C%20the%20Navy%20probably%20wouldn't%20need%20to%20rely%20on%20its%20SM-3s%20to%20counter%20this%20threat%20because%20an%20SM-2%20or%20SM-6%20would%20potentially%20do%20the%20trick.%20That%20means%20the%20Navy%20cannot%20afford%20to%20come%20up%20short%20on%20these%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269f4ae1b-95fe-4caf-97e4-45f25d97dc6e%5C%22%3E'Burning%20through'%20SM-3s%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20SM-3%20made%20its%20combat%20debut%20in%20April%2C%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Navy%20Carlos%20Del%20Toro%20told%20lawmakers%20that%20the%20sea%20service%20needs%20more%20of%20this%20interceptor%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-not-ready-china-war-military-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecounter%20potential%20future%20threats%20in%20the%20Pacific%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20China%2C%20which%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20identified%20as%20its%20%26quot%3Bpacing%20challenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223702%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20SM-3%20Block%201B%20interceptor%20missile%20is%20launched%20from%20the%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Lake%20Erie%20during%20a%20Missile%20Defense%20Agency%20and%20US%20Navy%20test%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66326ef210dfcda40965690c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222468%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUSS%20Lake%20Erie%20launches%20an%20SM-3%20during%20a%20test%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20truly%20believe%20that%20the%20SM-3s%20will%20be%20needed%20in%20greater%20numbers%20in%20the%20future%2C%20given%20the%20operations%20that%20took%20place%20in%20defense%20of%20Israel%2C%26quot%3B%20Del%20Toro%20said%20at%20the%20time.%C2%A0%26quot%3BRecently%2C%20some%20were%20fired.%20And%20very%20effectively.%20So%20I%20think%20given%20the%20future%20threat%20and%20our%20deterrence%20mission%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20need%20more%20SM-3s%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fiscal%20Year%202025%20defense%20budget%20proposal%20doesn't%20reflect%20that%20urgency%20though.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcomptroller.defense.gov%2FPortals%2F45%2FDocuments%2Fdefbudget%2FFY2025%2Fbudget_justification%2Fpdfs%2F02_Procurement%2FPROC_MDA_VOL2B_PB_2025.pdf%23page%3D155%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunclassified%20Pentagon%20budget%20documents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20will%20only%20produce%2012%20SM-3%20Block%20IIA%20annually%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20half%20of%20what%20was%20procured%20in%20FY2023%20and%20a%20drop%20from%20previous%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20huge%20concern%20that%20we%20are%20burning%20through%20SM-3s%20as%20fast%20as%20we%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Jim%20Fein%2C%20a%20research%20assistant%20for%20national%20security%20and%20European%20affairs%20at%20The%20Heritage%20Foundation%2C%20said.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20Standard%20Missile%20series%20is%20%26quot%3Bessential%26quot%3B%20for%20intercepting%20missiles%20launched%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-china-missile-problem-getting-worse-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina's%20massive%20rocket%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protect%20American%20assets%20such%20as%20warships%20and%20aircraft%20carriers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20exactly%20how%20many%20were%20used%20in%20repelling%20Iran's%20attacks%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20we%20are%20buying%20less%20than%2020%20per%20year%20and%20need%20thousands%20in%20case%20of%20a%20high-intensity%20conflict%2C%20like%20with%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Fein%20said.%20%26quot%3BEach%20expenditure%20really%20matters%2C%20even%20disregarding%20the%20cost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20anywhere%20enough%20SM-series%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20Fein%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20US%20is%20buying%20125%20SM-6s%20per%20year.%20And%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-aircraft-carrier-f-35-submarine-tomahawks-to-middle-east-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETomahawk%20Land%20Attack%20Missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20long-range%20cruise%20missiles%20designed%20by%20RTX%2C%20being%20produced%20has%20decreased%20annually%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222625%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20developmental%20Standard%20Missile-3%2C%20designed%20to%20intercept%20short%20to%20medium-ranged%20ballistic%20missile%20threats%2C%20is%20launched%20from%20the%20Pearl%20Harbor-based%20Aegis%20cruiser%20USS%20Lake%20Erie.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661ea66920b15f0ff4285f90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221992%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20SM-3%20is%20launched%20from%20USS%20Lake%20Erie.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20API%2FGamma-Rapho%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETomahawks%2C%20which%20aren't%20interceptors%20but%20rather%20long-range%20strike%20options%20that%20both%20surface%20warships%20and%20submarines%20can%20launch%2C%20have%20also%20been%20identified%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-submarines-getting-ship-killer-missile-able-to-counter-china-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euseful%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Navy%20would%20need%20in%20a%20potential%20war%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Iran's%20attack%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20US%20Sen.%20Roger%20Wicker%2C%20the%20Republican%20ranking%20member%20on%20the%20Senate%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSenatorWicker%2Fstatus%2F1842205616489517162%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%C2%A0%26quot%3Bexpended%20numerous%20SM-3%20Block%20IIA%20missiles%20defending%20Israel%26quot%3B%20and%20called%20on%20Congress%20to%20expand%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWicker%20also%20noted%20that%20Congress%20was%C2%A0%26quot%3Bpoised%26quot%3B%20to%20reject%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20proposal%20to%20cancel%20the%20SM-3%20Block%20IB%20production%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e102c4e4-a3a1-400d-b9de-9aefad86fd0d%5C%22%3EAlternatives%20to%20the%20more%20expensive%20interceptors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%20isn't%20meeting%20the%20current%20demand%20for%20air-defense%20interceptors%20or%20what%20it%20may%20need%20in%20a%20fight%20with%20China%2C%20Bryan%20Clark%2C%C2%A0a%20former%20Navy%20officer%20and%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%2C%20explained%20that%20there%20are%20alternatives%20to%20supplement%20those%20more%20expensive%20options%20being%20considered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221994%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Arleigh-Burke%20class%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Stout%20(DDG%2055)%20launched%20a%20Standard%20Missile%20(SM)%202%20during%20an%20exercise%20(MSLEX).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a31207a3c8094d5dcc72e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221488%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Arleigh-Burke%20class%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Stout%20launches%20an%20SM-2.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Lt.%20Laura%20Radspinner%2FReleased%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20biggest%20problems%20facing%20SM-series%20procurement%20are%20how%20expensive%20the%20missiles%20are%20%E2%80%94%20SM-6s%20and%20SM-2s%20run%20for%20%244%20million%20and%20%242%20million%2C%20respectively%20%E2%80%94%20and%20supply%20chain%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20designs%20of%20these%20missiles%20are%20finalized%20and%20tend%20to%20rely%20on%20very%20specific%20technologies%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20tend%20to%20rely%20on%20a%20generation%20of%20microelectronics%20that%20probably%20precedes%20what%20the%20current%20generation%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20that%20means%20those%20microelectronics%20tend%20to%20be%20fairly%20specialized%20and%20bespoke%2C%26quot%3B%20effectively%20meaning%20they%20need%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Btailor-made%26quot%3B%20for%20these%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReinvesting%20in%20adapting%20those%20designs%20to%20incorporate%20new%20technologies%20takes%20time%20and%20money%20and%20means%20the%20weapon%20has%20to%20be%20re-qualified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20that%20the%20most%20significant%20movement%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bthe%20transition%20from%20relying%20on%20these%20bespoke%2C%20highly%20integrated%2C%20highly%20sophisticated%20weapons%26quot%3B%20toward%20lower-cost%20options%2C%20such%20as%20unmanned%20systems%20or%20much%20cheaper%20missiles%2C%20that%20can%20be%20produced%20at%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20development%20would%20give%20US%20forces%2C%20in%20a%20fight%20with%20China%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20variety%20of%20air-defense%20options%20and%20reserve%20the%20high-value%20interceptors%20for%20when%20they%20need%20them%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-burns-through-key-missiles-needed-for-china-fight-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728633601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6707d40f3f2165d716dfc981%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-burns-through-key-missiles-needed-for-china-fight-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Conflicts%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20stockpiles%20of%20key%20interceptors%20the%20US%20would%20need%20in%20a%20high-end%20fight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jepstein%40businessinsider.com%20(Jake%20Epstein%2CChris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-burns-through-key-missiles-needed-for-china-fight-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Oberoi%20Realty%20to%20raise%20Rs%206%2C000%20cr%20via%20equity%20shares%2C%20securities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728633304000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-07%2F20%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F400X400%2F1721453495-016.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Foberoi-realty-to-raise-funds-of-rs-6-000-cr-124101100420_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20company%20may%20raise%20the%20amount%20in%20one%