d%20traditional%20healing%20practices%2C%20introducing%20modern%20medicine%20required%20thoughtful%20and%20respectful%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20tribes%E2%80%99%20reluctance%20melted%20into%20gratitude%2C%20the%20Bangs%20knew%20they%20were%20on%20the%20right%20path.%20Thirty-nine%20years%20ago%2C%20fresh%20out%20of%20the%20premier%20Johns%20Hopkins%2C%20they%20stood%20at%20the%20precipice%20of%20a%20sea%20of%20opportunities%2C%20each%20more%20lucrative%20than%20the%20other.%20But%2C%20an%20inner%20voice%20guided%20their%20next%20step%20%E2%80%94%20research%20is%20fruitful%20in%20areas%20where%20problems%20exist%2C%20not%20where%20facilities%20are%20ample.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20formed%20the%20backbone%20of%20their%20decision%20to%20head%20to%20the%20naxal-hit%2C%20Maoist%20Gadchiroli%20in%20Maharashtra.%20And%20their%20arrival%20was%20interpreted%20as%20a%20blessing.%20Since%20the%20outset%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20attempted%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F338010%2Fkerala-startup-mykare-building-uber-of-healthcare-for-surgeries%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eachieve%20health%20equity%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20relegating%20reductive%20healthcare%20to%20the%20boot%20and%20bringing%20in%20scientific%20discipline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20preliminary%20OPD%20(Out%20Patient%20Department)%20from%20which%20Dr%20Abhay%20and%20Dr%20Rani%20Bhang%20operated%20in%20Gadchiroli%20to%20treat%20tribal%20communities%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-2-1728467876-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-369362%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20preliminary%20OPD%20(Out%20Patient%20Department)%20from%20which%20Dr%20Abhay%20and%20Dr%20Rani%20Bang%20operated%20in%20Gadchiroli%20to%20treat%20tribal%20communities.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tribal%20pockets%20across%20India%2C%20high%20infant%20mortality%20rates%20(IMR)%20continue%20to%20perplex%20authorities%3B%20one%20of%20the%20many%20pressing%20issues.%20Studies%20suggest%20that%20over%2089%20percent%20of%20tribal%20women%20have%20anaemia%2C%20while%20only%2070.1%20per%20cent%20of%20tribal%20women%20deliver%20in%20an%20institution.%20Meanwhile%2C%20children%20from%20tribal%20communities%20were%20found%20to%20be%20almost%20one%20and%20a%20half%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20underweight%20than%20children%20from%20other%20communities.%20This%20owes%20to%20malnourished%20expectant%20mothers%2C%20a%20study%20found%2C%20whose%20findings%20revealed%20that%20only%2025%20percent%20of%20pregnant%20and%20lactating%20tribal%20women%20had%20adequate%20protein%20and%20calorie%20intake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20biggest%20killer%20is%20misinformation%2C%20Dr%20Rani%20remarked%20through%20her%20years%20of%20work%20with%20women%20in%20Gadchiroli.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20four%20major%20issues%20that%20I%20have%20seen%20women%20here%20face%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F143287%2Fup-menstruation-padman-school%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emenstrual%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reproductive%20tract%20infections%20that%20are%20manifested%20in%20the%20form%20of%20white%20discharge%2C%20uterine%20cancers%2C%20and%20infertility%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Rani%20shares.%20She%20spotlights%20the%20gaps%20and%20potential%20solutions%20that%20will%20better%20healthcare%20outcomes%20in%20tribal%20belts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAddress%20the%20gap%20in%20knowledge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMisinformation%20is%20benign%20until%20it%E2%80%99s%20not.%20As%20Dr%20Rani%20discovered%2C%20the%20cultural%20chasms%20of%20health%20are%20deep-rooted.%20Her%20conversations%20with%20women%20in%20Gadchiroli%20revealed%20that%20many%20of%20them%20consider%20%E2%80%98heavy%20menstruation%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20that%20most%20doctors%20would%20term%20%E2%80%98dangerous%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20healthy%20physiology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Rani%20Bhang%20is%20an%20MD%20in%20obstetrics%20and%20gynaecology%20and%20specialises%20in%20women's%20health%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-tribal-areas-3-1728467967-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Fhealthcare-access-in-